            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> The - on line 3 indicates that an open fold starts on line 3, the 2 indicates that it is contained in 2 additional folds.\n\nThat's correct for line 3, but what does the `2` on line 4 mean? Shouldn't it just be `3 ` instead of `23`?\n\n> Your expected behavior obfuscates the fact that line 3 is also contained in the folds starting on line 1 and 2.\n\nThat's also true. What about this?\n\n```\n- line 1\n|-line 2\n2-line 3\n3 line 4\n```\n\nOr attempting to fill `foldcolumn` as much as possible:\n\n```\n- line 1\n|-line 2\n2-line 3\n2|line 4\n```\n",
